com.gemstone.gemfire.modules.hibernate

Class EnumType

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.type.EnumType
      • com.gemstone.gemfire.modules.hibernate.EnumType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.hibernate.usertype.EnhancedUserType, org.hibernate.usertype.ParameterizedType, org.hibernate.usertype.UserType

    public class EnumType
extends org.hibernate.type.EnumType
    Extends EnumType so as to override methods responsible for cached representation of enums in hibernate. This class must be used in place of EnumType in client-server topology when the application classes are not available on the server. e.g. a typical enum configuration should look like this: 
     <property name="myEnum">
   <type name="com.gemstone.gemfire.modules.hibernate.EnumType">
     <param name="enumClass">com.mycompany.MyEntity$MyEnum</param>
     <param name="type">12</param>
   </type>
 </property>
